					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I can't think of a single game from the commercial NES era that did this. It might be that its occurrence (in roguelikes) was pretty underground up until Diablo, which is post-nes. But i don't know of a single homebrew that does this either. Is there something that's technically difficult with having a, say, schmup, generate a level procedurally on the NES? Or is it just simply because it's generally hard to device procedural level generation that can maintain the players' interest for more than a couple of minutes (in other words, more of a design question rather than a technical one)?</div>

					
